type: dataset
title: "Historical K-Index Research Program: Global Coordination Capacity 1810-2020"
abstract: >
  The Historical K-Index Research Program quantifies global coordination capacity
  from 1810-2020 using seven fundamental harmonies: governance, interconnection,
  reciprocity, complexity, knowledge, wellbeing, and evolutionary progression.
  This repository contains complete replication materials for a trilogy of papers:
  (1) Foundation paper establishing the K-index framework and validating all seven
  harmonies (1810-2020), (2) Regional divergence analysis examining coordination
  gaps across developed and developing regions, and (3) Temporal shocks study of
  crisis impacts on coordination resilience. Includes 191,913 raw data points,
  complete processing pipeline, and all figures/tables for Nature Sustainability
  submission.

