# Usage notes
notes: >
  This repository contains complete replication materials for a trilogy of papers
  examining global coordination capacity. Data files (~2.5 GB) are excluded from
  Git and available via Zenodo or download scripts. The repository uses a monorepo
  structure with shared data/code resources and paper-specific materials.

  **For Paper 1 users**: Complete K(t) time series 1810-2020 with all seven harmonies
  validated. Use shared/data/processed/k_index_final_1810_2020.csv as primary dataset.

  **For Paper 2 users**: Regional analysis builds on Paper 1 framework. Data structures
  support sub-national breakdowns where available.

  **For Paper 3 users**: Event study methodology uses same K(t) time series with
  high-frequency estimates during crisis periods.

  All data sources are publicly available with open licenses (primarily CC-BY-4.0).
  Complete reproducibility using provided Nix environment: `nix develop`.

